<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title><%= title %></title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/theme.css">
  <style>
    .tools-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap:18px; }
    .tool-card { background:#111; border:1px solid #1e1e1e; border-radius:14px; padding:22px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:12px; }
    .tool-card h3 { margin:0; color:#e8e8e8; }
    .tool-card p { color:#777; line-height:1.6; min-height:72px; }
    .tool-meta { color:#555; font-size:0.75rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.08em; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('partials/nav') %>

<div class="container" style="padding-top:24px">
  <div style="max-width:760px;margin-bottom:24px">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:8px">Tools</h2>
    <p>Operational tools and guided utilities live here. Timers are the first moved into this section, and the rest of the training helpers can expand here without cluttering the top nav.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tools-grid">
    <div class="tool-card">
      <div class="tool-meta">Training Utility</div>
      <h3>⏱ Timers</h3>
      <p>Round timer, interval timer, EMOM, AMRAP, and stopwatch for striking rounds, lifting blocks, circuits, and conditioning work.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/timers">Open Timers</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-card">
      <div class="tool-meta">Recovery Utility</div>
      <h3>🧘 Stretch Builder</h3>
      <p>Create warmup, cooldown, and mobility flows from exercise cards. Use it to build reusable prep and recovery routines just like saved workouts.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/stretch">Open Stretch</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-card">
      <div class="tool-meta">Planning Utility</div>
      <h3>📋 Training Plans</h3>
      <p>View assigned plans, phase structure, and scheduled sessions. This stays available as a tool even while the top-level nav is simplified.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/plans">Open Plans</a>
    </div>

    <div class="tool-card">
      <div class="tool-meta">Consistency Utility</div>
      <h3>🔥 Accountability</h3>
      <p>Review recent consistency, streaks, and session follow-through so the tools section also includes performance management, not just clocks.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="/accountability">Open Accountability</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>